cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.HC, cs.IR 

The paper focuses on analyzing online news usage patterns of two social groups, millennials and boomers, using passively metered usage data. This involves the use of computational methods and data analysis techniques, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.SD (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper also discusses the role of media infrastructures in shaping online news usage, which falls under the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper uses network analysis techniques to compare usage networks of the two social groups, which is a common method in the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
